<section id="faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<FaqItem question="What is the most common affiliate marketing mistake?">
<p>Choosing no niche or promoting unrelated products. Most beginners try to appeal to everyone and end up appealing to no one. A focused niche with targeted product recommendations consistently outperforms a broad approach.</p>
</FaqItem>

<FaqItem question="How do beginners succeed in affiliate marketing?">
<p>Beginners succeed by picking a narrow niche, building an email list from day one, committing to one traffic method for 6+ months, and following a structured training system rather than scattered free advice. Consistency beats intensity.</p>
</FaqItem>

<FaqItem question="Is affiliate marketing still profitable in 2026?">
<p>Yes, but the strategies have shifted. AI Overviews and Google HCU have reduced the effectiveness of thin-content SEO-only sites. Success in 2026 requires email building, traffic diversification, relationship-based promotion, and quality content that AI cannot replicate.</p>
</FaqItem>

<FaqItem question="How long does it take to make money with affiliate marketing?">
<p>Most successful affiliates see their first commission in months 3–6 and meaningful income at month 12+. The first 3 months should be treated as a learning period. Affiliate marketing compounds — the second year is significantly better than the first.</p>
</FaqItem>

<FaqItem question="What percentage of affiliate marketers fail?">
<p>Industry estimates suggest 90–95% of affiliates never make a significant income. The primary reasons are lack of structured training, quitting too early, and not building an email list. Following a proven system dramatically improves these odds.</p>
</FaqItem>
